# _defaults.env — every env var deploy-all.sh and deploy.sh understand.
#
# Do NOT source this directly. Copy one of the sibling profile files, edit the
# few placeholders, and `source config/<my-copy>.env` before ./deploy-all.sh.
#
# ============================================================================
# Universal (always required)
# ============================================================================
# AWS_REGION           default: your AWS CLI default region
# AWS_PROFILE          default: unset (use ambient creds)
# DOMAIN_NAME          Public FQDN devs connect to, e.g. claude-gateway.example.com
# PUBLIC_HOSTED_ZONE_ID  Route53 PUBLIC zone authoritative for DOMAIN_NAME
# ALLOWED_DOMAINS      Email domains permitted to sign in, comma-separated
# GATEWAY_IMAGE_URI    ECR URI of the gateway image (or set BUILD_IMAGE=true)
#
# ============================================================================
# Identity provider (IDP_MODE selects the path)
# ============================================================================
# IDP_MODE             "byo" | "new-cognito" | "existing-cognito"    (default: byo)
#
# --- byo (Okta/Entra/Google/Keycloak/existing Cognito you set up manually) ---
# OIDC_ISSUER              issuer URL (/.well-known/openid-configuration must resolve)
# OIDC_CLIENT_ID           confidential OIDC web client id
# OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET_ARN   Secrets Manager ARN holding the client secret
# GROUPS_CLAIM             groups claim name (Cognito=cognito:groups, Okta=groups, Entra=roles)
#
# --- new-cognito (stand up a fresh pool + client + admin user) --------------
# COGNITO_ADMIN_EMAIL      initial admin (emailed a temporary password)
# COGNITO_DOMAIN_PREFIX    globally-unique hosted-UI prefix, lowercase [a-z0-9-]{3,63}
#
# --- existing-cognito (attach a new client to a pool you already run) -------
# COGNITO_POOL_ID          e.g. us-east-1_xxxxxxxxx
#
# ============================================================================
# Telemetry (three modes, explicit)
# ============================================================================
# COLLECTOR_ENDPOINT   "off"                                 (recommended default)
#                    | "https://your.otel.example.com/"      (BYO — must be https)
#                    | (unset — same as off)
# ENABLE_COLLECTOR     "true" (deploys the bundled ADOT->CloudWatch collector)
#                    | "false"                                (default; use COLLECTOR_ENDPOINT for BYO)
#                    NOTE: only one of {COLLECTOR_ENDPOINT, ENABLE_COLLECTOR=true} at a time.
#                    ENABLE_COLLECTOR=true overrides COLLECTOR_ENDPOINT — the orchestrator
#                    deploys the bundle and injects its URL automatically.
# FORWARD_LOGS         "true" also forward audit EVENTS (tool decisions, auth,
#                      api_request/error) — powers the governance dashboard + alarms.
#                    | "false"  metrics only.  Default: true when ENABLE_COLLECTOR=true,
#                      else false. Events carry command/path metadata — see docs/CONFIG.md.
# ALARM_EMAIL          email subscribed to the collector's SNS alarm topic (default: none;
#                      topic is still created unsubscribed for you to wire to Slack/PagerDuty).
# DAILY_COST_THRESHOLD_USD  daily total-cost alarm threshold in USD          (default: 500)
# PER_USER_ALARM_EMAIL  raise a per-user daily-cost alarm on this user.email (alert-only,
#                      never blocks; fans out via its own SNS topic — hook Slack/PagerDuty/
#                      Lambda for downstream actionables). Empty = no per-user alarm.
# PER_USER_DAILY_THRESHOLD_USD  per-user daily cost that trips the alarm      (default: 88).
#                      Notify-only — never caps. Pair with a per-user amount:null spend
#                      override so the person is notified but never locked out.
#
# ============================================================================
# Spend caps (optional — HARD per-user/group/org budgets, enforced server-side)
# ============================================================================
# Telemetry/alarms above only TRACK + notify. These CAP: an over-budget developer
# gets 429 on their next request until the period resets. Caps are set AFTER deploy
# via the Admin API (POST /v1/organizations/spend_limits), not in these env vars —
# see docs/CONFIG.md and slides/DEMO-RUNBOOK.md.
# ENABLE_SPEND_CAPS    "true" (turn on the Admin API + enforcement) | "false" (default)
# GATEWAY_ADMIN_WRITE_KEY_ARN  Secrets Manager ARN of the admin write key (the x-api-key
#                      for the caps API). REQUIRED when ENABLE_SPEND_CAPS=true.
# SPEND_CAP_FAIL_CLOSED  "true" block requests if Postgres is unreachable during the cap
#                      pre-check (no unmetered spend) | "false" fail open (default; keeps
#                      inference up during a store outage).
# SPEND_BLOCKED_MESSAGE  text appended to the 429 a blocked developer sees (default: a
#                      "contact your platform team" message).
# ADMIN_GROUPS         comma-sep IdP groups granted full admin via their gateway JWT (no
#                      API key needed) — use for human FinOps admins. Default: none.
#
# ============================================================================
# Network access to the private ALB (BYO or bundle a Client VPN)
# ============================================================================
# CLIENT_CIDR          CIDR of remote clients allowed to reach the ALB on 443
#                      (default 10.30.0.0/16; matches the bundled VPN default)
# ENABLE_VPN           "true" (stand up bundled AWS Client VPN + emit .ovpn)
#                    | "false"                                 (default; BYO connectivity)
# VPN_CLIENT_NAME      client cert CN for the initial developer (default: developer1)
# VPN_CLIENT_CIDR      VPN client IP pool (default 10.30.0.0/22; must fit within CLIENT_CIDR)
#
# ============================================================================
# Image build (only used by deploy-all.sh)
# ============================================================================
# BUILD_IMAGE          "true" (build+push gateway image) | "false" (default; reuse existing)
# CLAUDE_VERSION       binary release pin when BUILD_IMAGE=true (default: 2.1.196)
# IMAGE_TAG            ECR tag (default: $CLAUDE_VERSION)
# ECR_REPO             (default: claude-apps-gateway)
#
# ============================================================================
# Scale / resilience (rarely changed; defaults are safe)
# ============================================================================
# MIN_TASKS            default: 2 (HA across AZs)
# MAX_TASKS            default: 10
# MULTI_AZ_DB          "true" | "false" (default false; recommend true in prod)
# BEDROCK_REGION       default: $AWS_REGION
# VPC_CIDR             default: 10.20.0.0/16
#
# ============================================================================
# Stack names (change to run multiple deployments side-by-side)
# ============================================================================
# GATEWAY_STACK        default: claude-gateway
# COGNITO_STACK        default: claude-gateway-cognito-client
# COLLECTOR_STACK      default: claude-gateway-collector
# VPN_STACK            default: claude-gateway-vpn
